This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to analyze the linguistic markers in news articles and tweets, which suggests that it belongs to the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper focuses on the interplay between mainstream and social media during political crises, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI, cs.SOC). The paper also involves analyzing a large dataset, which suggests that it could belong to the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the dynamics of partisan opinion formation and the potential for political slant in media, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
